<subSubSection lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="52" pageNumber="53" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="52" pageNumber="53">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="54" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">
Inhabits the evergreen foothill forests and lower evergreen montane forests throughout the Amazonian range from 1300-1800 m a.s.l. In the Andean region, it was recorded in the montane cloud forests from 1800-2080 m a.s.l. This species was 
<pageBreakToken pageId="53" pageNumber="54" start="start">collected</pageBreakToken>
with pitfall traps baited with human feces. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Rivera-Cervantes, LE" journalOrPublisher="Acta Zoologica Mexicana" pageId="276" pageNumber="277" pagination="23 - 150" title="Monografia de las especies Mexicanas de Canthon del subgenero Glaphyrocanthon." volume="77" year="1999">Rivera-Cervantes and Halffter (1999)</bibRefCitation>
, the previous records from Mexico are erroneous.
</paragraph>
